:"interface","displayName":"Chat Agent"},"detail":"docs\/ROADMAP.md","label":"read_file","status":"succeeded","id":"act-52"},{"kind":"systemMarker","speaker":{"icon":"point.3.connected.trianglepath.dotted","colorToken":"graphite","roleId":"foreman","kind":"system","displayName":"Foreman"},"detail":"allow read_file","label":"Operator gate","status":"succeeded","id":"act-53"}],"content":"Here's the full picture:\n\n---\n\n## Project: **Vokda** (`iksnae\/vokda`)\n\n**Vokda is the central destination for everything TTS** — a voice discovery and curation app. Think Pinterest for voices: browse, play, pin, organize, and export across 25 providers and 550 voices in 53 languages.\n\n### Stack\n| Layer | Tech |\n|-------|------|\n| Frontend | SvelteKit 4 (TypeScript, static adapter) on AWS Amplify |\n| Backend | SAM-deployed serverless (API Gateway + Lambda, Node 20) |\n| Data | AppSync + DynamoDB (12 tables), Cognito auth |\n| Audio | S3 (`vokda-audio-bucket`) for synthesized clips |\n| API Domain | `api.vokda.iksnae.com` |\n\n### Current State (March 2026)\n- **550 voices** across **25 providers**, 100% sample coverage\n- **9 synthesis adapters** (OpenAI, ElevenLabs, Deepgram, Gemini TTS, Cartesia, LMNT, GCP TTS, Azure Speech, AWS Polly)\n- SSML visual editor (7 tags, real-time validation)\n- Collections, favorites, cart + Voice Pack export, BYOK key management\n- **178 unit tests** passing\n- Auth live: visitor → guest → curator → admin hierarchy\n\n### Open Work\n| # | Type | Title | Phase |\n|---|------|-------|-------|\n| **#54** | Issue | Add `estimateReadingTime(text)` to text-utilities | `agencyx:review` |\n| **#55** | PR | AgencyX delivery — sweep-build-54 | Open (from #54 build) |\n| #1 | Issue | 🏭 Factory Roadmap | tracking |\n| #2 | Issue | 🏭 Curator Proposals | tracking |\n\nIssue #54 is the active work item — a small utility function that composes on `wordCount` to estimate reading time. The build PR (#55) is up for review.\n\n---\n\n## My Capabilities\n\nI'm the **Foreman** — your interface to the agency. Here's what I can do:\n\n### 🔍 Inspect & Understand\n- **Read\/search the codebase** — read files, search text\/code, find symbol definitions and references\n- **Recall the shadow brain** — see everything the agency has decided across this engagement\n- **Read GitHub issues\/PRs** in full, check CI status\n\n### 📋 Manage Work\n- **Create + queue issues** — file new work as scoped GitHub issues and kick them into the agency's pipeline\n- **Move issues through phases** (`new → product → planning → planned → ready → building → review → done`)\n- **Comment, close, reopen, assign, edit issues**\n- **Open PRs** for finished work\n\n### 🧠 Run Workflows\n- **`gate`** — Stage-1 intake: plan → verify → judge\n- **`planning`** — a validated plan\n- **`product`** — frame the product decision\n\n### 🛠 Skills (loadable playbooks)\n- **`geo-audit`** — Audit a product\/site for AI-assistant discoverability (GEO)\n\n### 📝 Record & Remember\n- **`record_decision`** — durable journal of what was decided and why\n- **`record_engagement_history`** — client-clean narrative of what was delivered\n\n### 🔧 Direct Edits (trivial\/immediate only)\n- Write\/edit files for small, explicit operator requests (anything substantial gets filed as an issue for the agency to build)\n\n---\n\nWhat would you like to tackle?"},{"id":"7A126709-204A-4462-9FD4-BD27CC27C4B8","role":"user","deliveryState":"complete","speaker":{"icon":"person.fill","colorToken":"accent","roleId":"operator","kind":"human","displayName":"Operator"},"at":804610533.021137,"activity":[],"content":"can u access ledger from vokda?"},{"id":"F7E37C79-DF24-4728-8F2D-D1AA532B354E","role":"assistant","deliveryState":"complete","speaker":{"roleId":"foreman","kind":"system","displayName":"Foreman","icon":"point.3.connected.trianglepath.dotted","colorToken":"graphite"},"at":804610533.021203,"activity":[{"detail":"Let me first ground myself in the project and shadow brain to understand what we'r